main event: An unidentified aerial object was observed over Albuquerque, New Mexico on February 25, 1950.
interesting points: The object was described as tear drop shaped with a core of greenish-white light,The object appeared to be about three times the size of a shooting star,The sighting lasted approximately 1.5 seconds,No sound or odor was reported during the sighting,The object was observed falling straight down, emitting a small trail.
sighted object: One tear drop shaped object with a greenish-white light
witness description: A student in Journalism at the University of New Mexico, interested in strange air phenomena
